Package: ALLSPICE
Type: Package
Title: ALLSPICE (ALLelic Spectrum of Pleiotropy Informed Correlated Effects)
Version: 0.1.2
Author: Wenhan Lu
Maintainer: The package maintainer <wlu@broadinstitute.org>
Description: ALLSPICE, a likelihood statistical test to identify allelic heterogeneity within a pleiotropic gene, defined as an imperfect correlation between the effects of variants within that gene on the two traits.It uses summary statistics from single-variant association tests and accounts for the phenotypic correlation. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
